description: Member of the Research and Development team that conducts research and reporting on elements operating against interests of the United States. As an analyst I assist with SIGINT development and reporting involving multiple targets which have received positive feedback from numerous high-level customers within the intelligence community. Work with DNI communication developing additional targets through research including collaborating with other analysts from across the IC.

description: Indoctrinated in to the National Security Agency January 2008. Assisted in quality control on mission critical reports in support of Operation ENDURING FREEDOM. Senior SGA analyst solely responsible for the detailed documentation of targets of interest telecommunications network. Developed network analysis to locate and identify targets of interest. Provided imagery used to identify and understand the telecommunication infrastructure and technologies used by a variety of targets of interest. Produced reporting and imagery to enable sustained collection and provide and intelligence through product reports, Requests for Information (RFI), and appropriate databases. Oversaw the Division-level digital network mission while actively engaging forward deployed elements, and supporting unit leaders and commanders with constant analysis of target communication in support of Operation IRAQI FREEDOM. description: Provided detailed SIGINT expertise and analysis in support of targeting operations of high-value individuals. Effectively synchronized the flow of intelligence information between SIGINT assets in theater and the NSA enterprise regarding high-valued targets within various insurgent groups. Provided time-sensitive reach back support for forward deployed analysts resulting in enhanced cooperation and support of targets of interest. I produced time-sensitive reports in support of combat and development missions.

description: - As the Subject Matter Expert and Senior Analyst of the S2 section, oversee the production and dissemination of analysis products - Acting PSG and NCOIC for the S-2 when needed; regularly interfaced and coordinated with the HQ Section Leaders to understand and meet the Squadron Commanders’ PIRs and CCIRs and remain flexible to needs - Coordinated with Brigade Level S-2 sections in creation and dissemination of intelligence products to meet the needs of Commanders at every level - Responsible for coordinating, developing, and implementing training plans for the S-2 such as intelligence refresher courses such as IPB and Open Source Intelligence Research - Produced a variety of overlay products such as MLCOA, MDCOA, Annex Bs, and various other intelligence products to be briefed by the S-2 OIC for 1-153 CAV Squadron Commander and Troop commanders - Conducted cultural, human terrain, and geospatial analysis of CENTCOM AORs, in support of ongoing military operations - Trained and mentored seven soldiers in the art of basic soldier skills to professional intelligence analysts - Responsible for over $500,000 of equipment with no loss or damage

description: - Nearly two years of experience supporting USSOCOM, CJSOTF, conventional, and OGA operations - DGS-SOF PED certified in Multi Source Intelligence Analyst (MSA), Screener (SCR), Full Motion Video (FMV), and as a MSA Instructor Rated Operator (IRO or trainer) crew positions - Created more than 500 products and have over 3000 hours conducting mission on Full Motion Video Process, Exploitation, and Dissemination (PED) lines with Air Force Special Operations Command (AFSOC) supporting manned and unmanned assets - Supported multiple Contingency operations such as TIC, PR events, C-IED, and other TSTs - Thorough understanding and experience with APG targeting and Find, Fix, Finish, Exploit, and Analyze (F3EA) SOF targeting cycle; Strong working relationship with SIGINT operators and the collection process and equipment - Extensive socio-cultural studies, research, and analysis of CENTCOM AOR such as Afghanistan, HOA, and North Africa including Pattern of Life and terrain analysis in support of Task Forces ops - First phase exploitation and Near Real Time (NRT) FMV analysis to Special Operations Forces; creates and reviews finished intelligence products, presentations and reports for special operations mission planning and time-sensitive execution - Conducted 2nd and 3rd phase analyst; identified intelligence gaps and worked with Fusion Cell (DOF) to fulfill RFIs by creating customized products from LiDAR and other imagery - FLT MSA Subject Matter Expert (SME) and MSA Lead IRO; attended Directorate of Training (DOT) positional working group meetings to discuss future training plans, as well as Courses of Action to enhance training and positional effectiveness - Vast experience and understanding of the Find, Fix, Finish, Exploit, and Analyze (F3EA) cycle - Side-saddle and OJT of exploitation and production of Geo-Spatial imagery

description: Assists higher level program/project manager in directing the project life cycle by assisting in development of comprehensive project plans to include both long and short-range goals and milestones. Identifies, acquires, and utilizes company resources to achieve project objectives. Directs a project team usually within a matrix organization, monitoring and encouraging functional organizations to complete milestones within specific budgets and schedules. May on occasion interface with external customers as well as top management for the purpose of communicating status of project throughout life cycle. May supervise direct reports. RESPONSIBILITIES: Defines, launches, and drives mission-critical strategic and operational initiatives in core non-technical programs. Creates a method of change management including ownership of a documentation library, communication plans, process training, etc. Matrix manages directors/managers from multiple departments to accomplish interdepartmental initiatives. Clearly documents and presents findings including creation of diagrams and procedure documentation. Responsible for driving recommendations through to implementation. Communicates effectively with a wide variety of technical and non-technical audiences. Identifies, analyzes and defines project requirements and scope. Exercises broadly delegated authority for planning, directing, coordinating, administering, and executing many routine and complex projects/programs. Assists with budget, staff, and other resources necessary to accomplish the goals and/or objectives of the program group/function. May develops performance plans and evaluations of employees, including subordinate supervisors as well as reviews evaluations to assure equity of individual employee performance objectives, standards and ratings among lower level staff/groups.

description: The Joint Expeditionary Team (JET) provides rapidly deployable expertise in all aspects of C-IED operations to support US Conventional and SOF forces worldwide. JET supports JIEDDO across three lines of operations: Attack the Network, Defeat the Device, and Train the Force. JET advisors assist and mentor units conducting offensive operations to proactively find, disrupt, and defeat IED networks; integrate and employ materiel and non-materiel solutions to detect and neutralize IEDs or mitigate their effects; and collect, analyze, and disseminate lessons learned and best practices observed during embedded operations to enhance combat unit proficiency in C-IED tactics, techniques, and procedures

description: Senior Analyst in support of Operation Iraq Freedom for Special Operations unit, Task Force Central as the Senior Targeting Analyst. My primary focus was the targeting of individuals responsible for the making of VBIED/IED/SVESTs etc. I also worked closely with Biometric teams, Technical IED teams, and Explosive Ordinance Disposal teams to track found or exploded IEDs back to the individual who made the IED. As the Senior HUMINT Analyst for the J2, I would train the new Intel Analysts on how all the different Intelligence practices work together (SIGINT, HUMINT, IMINT, ETC) and how they were utilized on a Special Operations level for targeting. I would assist during interrogations and I wrote a daily Executive Summary updating all the Battle Space Commanders of Special Operations Targets and Future Operations. I also assisted Human Intelligence collection resulting in the authoring and briefing of over 100 intelligence reports distributed throughout theatre.

description: E-CO 51st Long Range Surveillance, Task Force Phantom; Oct 2005-Apr 2007 96B/35F, A-CO 302nd MI BN; May 2003-Oct 2005 High Valued Individual Targeting Analyst (1 year tour Iraq) I was responsible for nominating V Corps' High Valued individuals (HVI) for targeting by my Task Force which I accompanied on all missions where I conducted field interrogations and gathered intelligence. I assisted in the screening of HUMINT sources and documents to build intelligence products and made recommendations based off my analysis for future operations. I created and implemented ISR Plans for operations targeting HVI’s using both Unmanned Ground Sensors (UGS) and Tagging, Tracking, and locating (TTL) equipment. HUMINT/All Source Analyst: I was responsible for researching and developing Intelligence displayed in Graphic Intelligence Summaries that I briefed to the Corps Commander daily on strategic issues in our area of operations, European Command. Worked with coalition forces, CIA, and the FBI, to produce link diagrams, extracting information from outside and internal resources, and generating finished PowerPoint presentations of completed products. Participated with FBI investigating corrupt individuals within in the Iraqi government and police organizations by producing target packages, map products, timelines, data-mining and generating final reports for investigative purposes.

description: Senior Intelligence Officer responsible for all Intelligence Operations for two subordinate Battalions and Detach-ments of the 29th Combat Aviation Brigade consisting of over 700 soldiers. description: Manages and monitors Multi-Service (Ravens Group, SAVA, FBI) contracts (e.g., multi-million dollar, Subject Matter Expertise Support, Management and Program Analysis, Policy Support, Knowledge Management and Strategic Communication Support, Training Support and Administrative Support associated with ongoing initiatives throughout the FBI-WMD Directorate). Develops and executes contract surveillance parameters. Analyzes and evaluates contract performance and makes recommendations for revisions. Provide contract administration actions such as investigation and resolution of contractor delays and contractor performance appraisal. Plans and conducts conferences with contractors and government personnel to assure compliance with, and full understanding of, contractual requirements and to preclude unauthorized changes or alterations to the contract. Maintain surveillance of contract elements, such as compliance with applicable laws, specifications, performance schedules, and payment provisions, to include actions to ensure that Government project officer and assigned personnel adequately perform delegated functions. Provide centralized oversight, prioritization, and tracking of contracts. Maintain database of contracts. Track disbursements of contracts to prevent over/under spending. Provide technical advice and guidance to personnel to ensure conformance with policy directives, recommendations, and decisions. Advise FBI-WMD Directorate and other vendors regarding Multi-Service contracts to include award fee, modifications, surveillance activities, con-tract research.

description: Operations Officer in a fast-paced, multidisciplinary environment to support personnel and financial management, planning, and program integration for Identity Resolution Exploitation Management Services (IREMS) initiatives. Serves as the principal staff officer to IREMS Chief/Project Manager in all matters concerning operations, plans, and organization that affect or impact on all organizational activities in the Line of Operation (LOO). Has an inherent responsibility for coordination with members of COCOMS, TRADOC, ARSTAFF, JIEDDO, DoD, and other government agencies. Provides executive level advice and assistance to the Director of IREMS on a variety of mission related administrative policy matters and subjects. Performs duties and special functions in planning, organizing, tasking, guiding, and controlling the IREMS significant activities and actions across the Army G2/G38 directorates. Monitors policy and action item execution and compliance. Serves as the single face into IREMS for FORSCOM, TRADOC, Assistant Secretary of the Army for Acquisitions, Logistics, and Technology (ASAALT), Army Material Command (AMC), Headquarters Department of the Army (HQDA), Foreign Governments, and Other Government Agencies (OGA). Advises IREMS management on polices, current attitudes, and expressed desires.

description: Interacts directly with the unit Commanders and JIEDDO C-IED Operations/Intelligence Integration Center (COIC) during the development of intelligence products that respond to Company, Battalion, Division or MEF, and Special Forces Requests for Support (RFS). Coordinate the support packages provided to meet unit and subordinate element operational requirements. Assist’s in fusing the operational and intelligence information available to the supported unit, providing an operational perspective to the products that the supported commander and COIC deliver, including target and network analysis packages. Play major role in assisting unit elements in the formulation and integration of RFSs to the COIC throughout the operational planning cycle. Assist units in Afghanistan with the C-IED/Counterinsurgency fight as part of a deployed multi-disciplined section. Support the BCT Commander across the Brigade in order to provide a capability in immediate proximity to enable real time support and analysis of issues addressing war-fighter’s needs. o Collect, analyze and fuse operational and intelligence information to assist the BCT in planning, targeting, and conducting missions. o Assist the unit as a C-IED/Counterinsurgency SME with relevant techniques, tactics and procedures (TTP). o Routinely collaborate with the SOF and provide a reach-back capability for support from the Counter IED Operations Integration Center (COIC), and other JIEDDO/DOD entities. o Guide and advise the C-IED working groups, and route clearance team utilization. o Provide trends/patterns analysis, and geospatial mapping visualizations. o Present recommendations for utilization of ISR, UGS, and JIEDDO Alternate Compensatory Control measure (ACCM) Programs and assets. o Share comprehensive and in depth knowledge of the IED Defeat lines of operations (Attack the Network, Defeat the Device, and Train the Force).

description: Lead, supervise, and manage operations of three-member Human Intelligence (HUMINT) Collection Team gathering information from across seven provinces in Afghanistan to support military objectives. Coordinate with Special Operation Task Forces and supported units to collect and assess validity of information from HUMINT sources; conduct training, mission planning, sensitive site exploitation, and source and detainee operations. Review all team analyses and reports; identify patterns, trends, and key elements of intelligence, and brief coalition leaders. Maintain accountability for contingency funds and $250K+ in equipment. ** Excelled in Military Source Operations leadership role; built source network of 17+ active contacts, including two Category 2 contacts. ** Collected and disseminated 350+ intelligence reports, providing accurate, actionable intelligence to commanders in the field; impacted detainment of nine individuals associated with insurgent activities. ** Supervised group’s only team to identify, nominate, and target High Value Targets (HVTs) through internal HUMINT collection and analysis, creating successful team-level targeting cycle. ** Founded intelligence sync meeting with Special Forces, OGA, counter-intelligence, and signal intelligence (SIGINT) to provide combined, robust situational reports for intelligence customers. ** Created cross-training to enhance team’s tactical questioning skills, and implemented special operation standards for sensitive site exploitation into tactical SOPs. ** Identified communication shortcomings within unit; developed SOP to mitigate loss of effectiveness in the event of communications equipment failure. ** Implemented use of sand tables and static rehearsals to improve team performance during training exercises; developed practical classified training exercise to illustrate proper reporting formats.

description: Conducted mission planning, site exploitation, and source and detainee operations to support surveillance operations in Iraq as member of HUMINT Collection Team; tracked enemy actions and compiled analytical products to validate sources and corroborate intelligence reporting. ** Presented intelligence reporting for 45+ patrols, heightening situational awareness and increasing safety for personnel working in the field. ** Selected to brief executive leadership on enemy networks, corruption / infiltration of Iraqi police, and other key intelligence, enabling unit to prevent movement of explosives throughout the area. ** Generated source network from scratch by engaging effectively with local populace, and leveraged network for exceptional productivity, generating more than 50% of team’s intelligence reports. ** Produced intelligence reports on locations of enemy activities that led to discovery of five weapons caches, creating safer operating environment for both U.S. and Iraqi forces. ** Developed training program for Company Level Intelligence Support Team; provided guidance on building target packets that led to capture of escaped prisoner from Ninewa Provincial Prison. ** Examined base layout, identified security threats, and recommended solutions to mitigate risks; created and implemented new SOPs and training for entry point screening, source handling, security procedures, and communication systems operations.

description: BOARD OF DIRECTORS - Selected and unanimously voted to be approved as an acting Board member for the prestigious organization known as, The Specialist Training Association. This Board consists of vetted and seasoned professionals from within the fields of Security, Law Enforcement, Intelligence, Counter-Terrorism, Military, Hand2Hand Combat, etc. The Industry looks upon the Board to set forth and uphold the requirements and standards needed for licensure, continuous training, certifications, and ensures that at least, the minimum requirements are being met. The Board also has within its discretion the right to revoke such licensing if at the very least the minimum standards are not being upheld or mitigating circumstances arise unbecoming of a person/s that discredit the industry or profession.

description: Graduate of the State Department's WPPS High Threat Protection Academy. Provided in-transit security for precious cargo to include high end explosives. Selected, vetted, and trained an Iraqi guard force of over 60 personnel, including procurement of weapons, maintaining large cash budgets, and provided site security leadership of over 30 US personnel, US Army Corps. Of Engineers, and total local national support personnel of over 100 people without one incident. All during the large combat uprising of the Mahdi Militia in An-Nasariya. Served for two US Ambassadors to Iraq on the Ambassadors Protective Detail. Both Mr. John Negropante and Mr. Khalizad. I've been in drivers positions, I.e. limo motorcade, follow vehicle motorcade, as well as door gunner and various Psd positions to include Team Leader. I have also performed overwatch counter sniper missions and served on the advanced team and the future site reconnaissance team. I am held in high regard by my superiors and teammates as a person of integrity and trust in addition to being tactically proficient in all aspects of security especially operating in combat zones, and austere environments.

description: Served as a police officer in Norfolk, Va. Became member of elite unit with concentration on self generated cases, targeting high crime and gang infested areas utilizing surveillance, plain clothes operations and unmarked police vehicles. Decorated with a unit Life Saving Medal for pulling a hanging subject from a rope three stories high back through a window after his suicide attempt and performing CPR resulting in him living to fight another day. Worked as a police officer in the St. Louis County, Mo. areas. Decorated and recognized for locating and arresting a suspect during surveillance which was found to be the sole perpetrator of over 20 uncleared, 'smash n grab' burglaries. That arrest cleared open cases in over five or more jurisdictions and shut down an 'underground' illegal cigarette selling operation. Also worked special undercover, plain clothes details targeting high value target suspects.

description: Communications specialist at ComnavspecwarDevgru, tasked with the overall inventory, team budget, team training, and procurement of specific mission essential equipment as it related to our current and future mission status changes. As a communications Team Lead Petty Officer I was in charge of all new research, development, testing and evaluation (RDT&E). This was performed utilizing various platforms, I.e., boats, fixed and rotary aircraft, water borne ops, land nav ops, etc. I maintained weapons proficiency as well as attending professional shooting schools and obtaining my accelerated freefall qualification (AFF). I received several citations and medals including the Joint Service Achievement Medal. I worked with numerous branches of military within the specops specwar community. In addition, I traveled extensively and worked with several foreign military units, always promoting a positive and professional image.

description: Individually selected to spearhead the All-Source analysis effort for the Network Analysis Cell, CJ2 Kandahar Intelligence Fusion Center (KIFC), Combined Joint Task Force-10 (CJTF-10). Produced multiple Targeting Intelligence Packets/Target Support Packets, Social Network Diagrams, Interrogation Support Packets/ SDRs for detainee exploitation, and 400 RFIs incorporating GEOINT, SIGINT, Biometrics, TECHINT, and HUMINT in support of 10th Mountain and it’s subordinate units in Regional Command-South (RC-S) area of operations. Operated in coordination with OGA, NSA, NGA, DEA, DIA and FBI personnel to provide counterinsurgency support to Combined Joint Task Force-10 as the 10th MTN DIV (LI) Analysis and Control Element's (ACE) Master Analyst. Created, implemented, and supervised the Distributed Common Ground System – Army (DCGS-A) and ACE Block II system architecture for the RC-S Headquarters, applying first-ever employed designs to overcome regional-level challenges during combat operations. Personally directed the efforts of over 20 technical experts to field DCGS-A on the battlefield and commended by the ISAF CJ2 for excellence and technical expertise.

description: • As an Intelligence Chief in Department of State’s aviation department, monitored current intelligence of specified targets, providing threats assessments, focused on aircraft operators and infrastructure. • Performed duties such as: maintain database on specified aerial intelligence, process current and historical data collected, and request information from internal and external agencies. • Continuously generated intelligence-based assessments, used by tactical operators and operational planners during the mission-planning cycle. Analyzed operational needs to determine functional and cross-functional intelligence requirements and their relationship to operations.

description: • Served as an Intelligence Analyst, responsible for receiving and processing message traffic from outside intelligence agencies, preparing and presenting briefs, and creating daily intelligence summaries. • Conducted analysis on the effects of Anti-Iraqi Forces (AIF) operations towards the regional reconstruction effort, including cultural, religious, political, geo-political, military/social/behavioral science and perspectives on governance and development. • Prepared analytical reports, charts, tables, graphs, publications and developed target profile analyses, including anticipatory activity and projections according to reliability and sensitivity.

description: • Held responsible for researching, developing, presenting and publishing all-source intelligence products at the tactical, operational and strategic level related to Military actions, insurgent activities, economic and political activities, and threats to regional stability as part of an overall analytical team. • Responsible for analysis, reporting, databasing and dissemination of intelligence measures of stability which include security, governance and development, Human Terrain Analysis, preparation of provincial and district assessments, and Mission Analysis briefings, High Value Individual Targeting products, Extremist and Regional Threat Network Nodal Analysis, and preparation of Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance Assessment Metrics. • As the lead targeting analyst, created target packages on high value targets within the unit’s AO that were based upon SIGINT, IMINT, HUMINT, UAV surveillance and SOF reporting. • Served as a Collections analyst creating and maintaining continuous targeting decks for intelligence platforms while working with outside intelligence agencies to plan prepare and execute scheduling requirements on multiple intelligence platforms to maintain continuity of the area of operations. • Served as a Battalion Support Team (BST) Chief within the Tactical Fusion Center managing a six man intelligence team responsible for the collection, production, and dissemination of all intelligence products to the Division staff.

description: Requested support from assets such as the U-2, JSTARS, SENTINEL, MC-12, MQ-1, MQ-9, Blue Devil, Aces HY, Gorgon Stare, Constant Hawk, Other WAAS/WAMI assets, and RQ-4. Responsible for coordinating all C-IED Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) collection requirements and ensured all intelligence data was properly disseminated within the supported command/organization. Developed, maintained and updated collection plans based on the supported Commander's Priority Intelligence Requirements in support of C-IED specific targets, and monitored a wide range of available organic and non-organic collection systems. Supported newly nominated/emerging requirements then validated and distributed accordingly. Prepared ISR assessment metrics of IMINT, SIGINT and HUMINT products to evaluate and gauge the effectiveness of collection operations. Interacted with higher, lateral and subordinate Commands/Organizations' collection and requirements managers including entities within ANSF/GIRoA to answer intelligence related RFIs and de-conflict or collaborate on AOR C-IED requirements and reporting. Provided SOF/OGA teams with mission critical ISR over-watch and collection strategies that resulted in numerous HVT (High Value Targets) capture. Maintain daily contact with intelligence analysts and collection strategists that focus on the CIED networks. Apply multi-discipline, all source, and general military intelligence collection management methodologies and techniques to support analysis and characterization of Improvised Explosive Devices using biometric tags and forensics to counter and defeat the threat in Afghanistan.

description: Worked directly in support of aircraft such as the U-2, JSTARS, MC-12, MQ-1, MQ-9, and RQ-4. Provided direct Request for Information (RFI) support to CJSOTF, SOTF-E, SOTF-S and multinational forces in support of Operation Enduring Freedom (OEF). Produced several ISR based fusion products to include; HUMINT, SIGINT, GMTI, IMINT, and other geospatial intelligence in response to ADHOC requests in support of the Air Force customer requirements. Produced pre-mission briefings, weekly activity reports (WARs), storyboards, current intelligence briefs and other associated products. Correlated and fused information from Imagery Intelligence (IMINT), Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) and other sources to provide tailored, regionally-focused analysis reports to support mission operations. Was Responsible for ISR derived Counter Improvised Explosive Device (CIED) tactical analysis Reports, incorporating fused intelligence from All-Source, SIGINT, and IMINT databases within close proximity to suspected IED related activity. Interacted with and shared fused products with multiple intelligence agencies.

description: Work in direct support of the Airscan,MQ-1, MQ-9, IGNAT, Greendart, and Guardrail. Assessed lines of operations (LOO) of Foreign Fighter/Weapons Facilitators as well as other Al Qaeda in Iraq (AQI) Extremists. Familiar with the Find, Fix, Finish, Exploit, Analyze, and Disseminate (F3EAD) targeting process. Built status reports and target packages of personalities using Microsoft PowerPoint and Analyst Notebook, which were briefed to the Commander in daily targeting meetings. Provided SDRs and feedback on Objectives in order to derive specific intelligence information from detained personalities. Engaged multiple Intelligence Agencies to conduct investigations and interrogations on detained high value targets (HVT). Generated the high value individual (HVI) Targeting Deck, which reflects HVI personality priority in Northern Iraq. Provided actionable intelligence to CJSOTF, SOTF-N, SFODA, OGA and ORA on HVIs through direct relationship.

description: Developed, and administered DoD collateral security programs and procedures for classified or proprietary materials, documents, and equipment. Studied and implemented Department of Defense (DOD) security regulations that apply to unit operations. Obtained rulings, interpretations, and acceptable deviations for compliance with regulations from DOD. Prepared policies outlining regulations, and establishes procedures for handling, storing, and keeping records, and for granting personnel and visitors access to restricted records and materials. Sets up and maintains DoD closed areas. Develops and provides security classification guidance including developing DD254s. Conducts security education training and security audits. Investigates security violations and prepares reports specifying preventive action to be taken. Interfaced with all levels of leadership and provided guidance and assistance. Understands the NISPOM and other applicable DoD regulations.

description: Work in direct support of the Airscan,MQ-1, MQ-9, IGNAT, Greendart, and Guardrail. Assessed routes used by Commander when traveling out of secure perimeter. Completed a nightly significant activity roll up for all FOBs in Iraq, using Microsoft Office and Webtas. Disseminated the nightly product to HUMINT teams in theatre for their situational awareness. Produced convoy briefs using CIDNE, and Geoquest. Briefed the current enemy threat as well as identified areas with intense enemy activity to commander during convoy briefings. description: Individually selected to spearhead the All-Source analysis effort for the Network Analysis Cell, CJ2 Kandahar Intelligence Fusion Center (KIFC), Combined Joint Task Force-10 (CJTF-10). Produced multiple Targeting Intelligence Packets/Target Support Packets, Social Network Diagrams, Interrogation Support Packets/ SDRs for detainee exploitation, and 400 RFIs incorporating GEOINT, SIGINT, Biometrics, TECHINT, and HUMINT in support of 10th Mountain and it’s subordinate units in Regional Command-South (RC-S) area of operations. Operated in coordination with OGA, NSA, NGA, DEA, DIA and FBI personnel to provide counterinsurgency support to Combined Joint Task Force-10 as the 10th MTN DIV (LI) Analysis and Control Element's (ACE) Master Analyst. Created, implemented, and supervised the Distributed Common Ground System – Army (DCGS-A) and ACE Block II system architecture for the RC-S Headquarters, applying first-ever employed designs to overcome regional-level challenges during combat operations. Personally directed the efforts of over 20 technical experts to field DCGS-A on the battlefield and commended by the ISAF CJ2 for excellence and technical expertise.

description: Requested support from assets such as the U-2, JSTARS, SENTINEL, MC-12, MQ-1, MQ-9, Blue Devil, Aces HY, Gorgon Stare, Constant Hawk, Other WAAS/WAMI assets, and RQ-4. Responsible for coordinating all C-IED Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) collection requirements and ensured all intelligence data was properly disseminated within the supported command/organization. Developed, maintained and updated collection plans based on the supported Commander's Priority Intelligence Requirements in support of C-IED specific targets, and monitored a wide range of available organic and non-organic collection systems. Supported newly nominated/emerging requirements then validated and distributed accordingly. Prepared ISR assessment metrics of IMINT, SIGINT and HUMINT products to evaluate and gauge the effectiveness of collection operations. Interacted with higher, lateral and subordinate Commands/Organizations' collection and requirements managers including entities within ANSF/GIRoA to answer intelligence related RFIs and de-conflict or collaborate on AOR C-IED requirements and reporting. Provided SOF/OGA teams with mission critical ISR over-watch and collection strategies that resulted in numerous HVT (High Value Targets) capture. Maintain daily contact with intelligence analysts and collection strategists that focus on the CIED networks. Apply multi-discipline, all source, and general military intelligence collection management methodologies and techniques to support analysis and characterization of Improvised Explosive Devices using biometric tags and forensics to counter and defeat the threat in Afghanistan.

description: Worked directly in support of aircraft such as the U-2, JSTARS, MC-12, MQ-1, MQ-9, and RQ-4. Provided direct Request for Information (RFI) support to CJSOTF, SOTF-E, SOTF-S and multinational forces in support of Operation Enduring Freedom (OEF). Produced several ISR based fusion products to include; HUMINT, SIGINT, GMTI, IMINT, and other geospatial intelligence in response to ADHOC requests in support of the Air Force customer requirements. Produced pre-mission briefings, weekly activity reports (WARs), storyboards, current intelligence briefs and other associated products. Correlated and fused information from Imagery Intelligence (IMINT), Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) and other sources to provide tailored, regionally-focused analysis reports to support mission operations. Was Responsible for ISR derived Counter Improvised Explosive Device (CIED) tactical analysis Reports, incorporating fused intelligence from All-Source, SIGINT, and IMINT databases within close proximity to suspected IED related activity. Interacted with and shared fused products with multiple intelligence agencies.

description: Work in direct support of the Airscan,MQ-1, MQ-9, IGNAT, Greendart, and Guardrail. Assessed lines of operations (LOO) of Foreign Fighter/Weapons Facilitators as well as other Al Qaeda in Iraq (AQI) Extremists. Familiar with the Find, Fix, Finish, Exploit, Analyze, and Disseminate (F3EAD) targeting process. Built status reports and target packages of personalities using Microsoft PowerPoint and Analyst Notebook, which were briefed to the Commander in daily targeting meetings. Provided SDRs and feedback on Objectives in order to derive specific intelligence information from detained personalities. Engaged multiple Intelligence Agencies to conduct investigations and interrogations on detained high value targets (HVT). Generated the high value individual (HVI) Targeting Deck, which reflects HVI personality priority in Northern Iraq. Provided actionable intelligence to CJSOTF, SOTF-N, SFODA, OGA and ORA on HVIs through direct relationship.

description: Developed, and administered DoD collateral security programs and procedures for classified or proprietary materials, documents, and equipment. Studied and implemented Department of Defense (DOD) security regulations that apply to unit operations. Obtained rulings, interpretations, and acceptable deviations for compliance with regulations from DOD. Prepared policies outlining regulations, and establishes procedures for handling, storing, and keeping records, and for granting personnel and visitors access to restricted records and materials. Sets up and maintains DoD closed areas. Develops and provides security classification guidance including developing DD254s. Conducts security education training and security audits. Investigates security violations and prepares reports specifying preventive action to be taken. Interfaced with all levels of leadership and provided guidance and assistance. Understands the NISPOM and other applicable DoD regulations.

description: Work in direct support of the Airscan,MQ-1, MQ-9, IGNAT, Greendart, and Guardrail. Assessed routes used by Commander when traveling out of secure perimeter. Completed a nightly significant activity roll up for all FOBs in Iraq, using Microsoft Office and Webtas. Disseminated the nightly product to HUMINT teams in theatre for their situational awareness. Produced convoy briefs using CIDNE, and Geoquest. Briefed the current enemy threat as well as identified areas with intense enemy activity to commander during convoy briefings. Researched multiple enemy weapon systems including (EFP, IRAM, IED, etc) and Summarized for the Commander.

description: Program Management and Systems Integration/Engineering of 7 JIEDDO experimental Radar, EW, SIGINT, HSI, S/LWIR, Special Payload CIED Air ISR programs worth >$250M; cost fund estimation, program budget analysis, program scheduling, research and development, rapid prototyping, and technical integration in direct support of Executive and Congressional decision making. Briefs Congress, OSD, and JIEDDO Director on Rapid Acquisition Strategy, CONOPS, Test and Evaluation Plan, Technical Integration Plan, Budget Analysis and Program Risk for rapid funding approval from Pre-Solution Refinement thru T3C. OCONUS Program Manager and Lead Operations Research Systems Analyst (ORSA) for CJTF-Paladin in OEF. Program oversight; recruits, manages and evaluates 40 ORSAs to execute a program budget of $65M. Interfaces with executive staff on program execution, budget, staffing, and business development. Provides ORSA support to the CJTFP Commander and staff on the evolution of the counter-IED fight in Afghanistan using Microsoft Suite, ArcGIS, WebTAS, CIDNE, ANB, and Palantir for analysis. Leads rapid response analysis efforts to address the immediate and pressing issues of the CJTF-Paladin Commander. Collates ORSA, DAC, WTI, CJ2 products for command review to ensure proper decision making, while servicing the Intel community with RFI/RFS answers. Helps to develop and implement improved reporting capabilities in the CENTCOM directed IED database of record in Afghanistan, improving the data set. Provides an assessment of CJTF-Paladin's effectiveness in the counter-IED fight. Assesses the effectiveness of several forward deployed material counter-IED initiatives procured by JIEDDO; including test planning, test data collection, and test data analysis. Interfaces directly with ISAF/NATO partners operating throughout Afghanistan and provides direct analytical support of ongoing operations. Provides counter-IED analytical support to multiple agencies.

description: Lead all-source intelligence analyst for the CJSOTF-A J2 External Areas of Influence (AI) Cell, conducting analysis of regional countries within the Middle East, South Asia, Central Asia, etc. that influence operations in Afghanistan. Coordinate with ISAF, NATO, IJC, DoD, IC, and other counterparts to satisfy command objectives. Provide daily updates for the J2 Staff and produce multiple finished products on a weekly basis. Develop collection strategies, conduct research, and produce long-term strategic regional assessments on countries impacting the operational environment in and around Afghanistan. Utilize systems such as Palantir, TAC, Google Earth, M3, QuerryTree, and Microsoft Office Suite. From OCT13 to Mid-NOV13, acted as the CJSOTF-A J2 JISE All-Source Production Lead. Reviewed, edited, and finalized all Graphical Intelligence Summaries, Commander's Update Briefs, and RFI responses. Ensured quality and content conformed with J2 OIC/NCOIC expectations; provided guidance and mentored both junior military and contractor analysts.

description: As an all-source intelligence analyst supporting CJSOTF-A, works with a team to research, analyze, present, and publish all source targeting analysis and intelligence production in support of operationally deployed special operations forces in the SOTF-S area of operations. Supports Targeting Effects Synchronization in support of future operations by identifying and developing actionable targets in AO. Develop IPOEs in support of combined USSF/ANASOF missions being conducted in SOTF-S AO. Develop enemy most likely/most dangerous course of action to support operational planning for VSO expansion. Travel as required to SOTF and forward units to conduct intelligence exchange and act as CJOSTF-A representative for briefings. Coordinate with NGA, OGA, ORSA, DIA, COIC, MASINT, and TCAE analysts on a daily basis collaborating with other ISAF SOF elements for intelligence sharing. Identify and track key personalities, named areas of interest, and compounds of interest to support targeting efforts. Utilize systems such as Palantir, TAC, Google Earth, M3, QuerryTree, and Microsoft Office Suite.

description: As a Department of the Navy (DoN), Damage Assessment Management Office (DAMO) Cyber Intelligence analyst, works with a team to provide analysis, estimates, and assessments in support of the DAMO mission – assessing the damage caused by the exfiltration of critical program information from cleared defense contractor (CDC) systems by foreign computer network attack (CNA) groups. Coordinate with Office of the Secretary of Defense (OSD) and other service DAMOs to facilitate review of compromised data for DoN cases. Work with NCIS, FBI, DSS, and other LE/CI and IC organizations to determine threat to CDC systems based on adversarial Computer Network Operations (CNO).

description: Supports the USCG and DHS international port security programs. Develops analytical judgments regarding the presence, intent, and capabilities of terrorist and criminal organizations, state and non-state adversaries, smugglers, and other offenders seeking to damage, illegally exploit, or disrupt components of the port transportation systems or visiting ships. Assesses threats to a foreign port, or threats exportable to the US carried by ships calling at that port. Utilizes multiple unclassified and classified systems to conduct research, identify intelligence gaps, evaluate reporting, and draft products illustrating threats to senior government decision makers. Coordinate research and findings with strategic, operational, and tactical level entities throughout the IC, DOD, and DHS.

description: Provide commercial maritime intelligence analysis and reporting within the ONI Civil Maritime Counter-Proliferation Division (ONI-114). Conduct research, collate, review, interpret, evaluate, and integrate data from multiple sources and provide assessments on relevant and significant maritime developments as it relates to proliferation conducted in the maritime domain. Prepare and conduct Maritime Intelligence reports, briefings, studies and trend analysis, estimates, and evaluations. Provide analysis on intelligence gaps, develop collection strategies and requirements, and levy analytical tools and methodologies to fill those gaps. Conduct extensive interagency coordination in support of Policy entities, NSC, IC Community partners, and the US Naval Commands. Attend meetings and conferences internal to ONI, within the IC community, and with Coalition counterparts. Assist with the management of eight other CMA personnel and produce the required Monthly Technical Reports. Statement of Work was modified to allow supervisory responsibilities of four government employees attached to ONI-114 PACOM Team. Responsibilities included development of yearly production plan, training schedule, conference attendance, and the review/development of junior analyst professional capabilities.

description: Supervised and directed office personnel responsible for handling clearance related issues for 15,000 forward deployed DoD military and contractor personnel as well as Coalition military personnel, providing clearance verification determination allowing/denying access to US Embassy, Baghdad. Performed SCI level indoctrinations and debriefs; processed Visit Certification, Permanent Certification, and Transfer in Status messages for afore mentioned personnel. Acted as preliminary investigator for all security violations originating or involving Multi-National Force – Iraq forward Headquarters or the US Embassy, Baghdad. Conducted Indications and Warnings analysis of threat reporting involving counter-terrorism, counter-proliferation, counter-piracy, and counter-drug operations. Responsible for providing fleet and theater intelligence centers with actionable maritime intelligence and providing coordination between USN and pertinent IC agencies. Routinely briefed Director of Naval Intelligence (DNI) and Senior ONI leadership on emerging maritime intelligence issues. Provided all source tactical level intelligence to pilots and electronic counter measure officers in support of combat operations: - Operation Enduring Freedom, Deployed USS Carl Vinson (AUG 2001 – JAN 2002), Duties included: Maritime Interdiction Operation support, Shipboard Reconnaissance and Recognition Team (SNOOPIE Team), and Assistant Targeteer. - Operation Iraqi Freedom, Deployed USS Nimitz (MAR 2003 – NOV 2003): Night shift supervisor of Mission Brief / Debrief and SNOOPIE Team Lead.

description: Provided all-source intelligence support to a joint headquarters responsible directly to the National Command Authority for strategic operations of national significance. Served as a core member of the Joint Planning Group (JPG), performing time-sensitive and enroute mission planning that enabled U.S. Special Operations Command’s elite units to conduct highly specialized, surgical, and sensitive operations worldwide. Provided Intel targeting support for operations against Afghan and Iraqi high value targets. As the senior intelligence officer aboard the airborne Command and Control platform during the initial assault into Afghanistan, fused all-source intelligence, dynamically re-tasked ISR assets and nominated targets for fires. Deployed as the lead DoD Intelligence officer to an Interagency Task Force that included the FBI and NYPD law enforcement.

description: Worked with the Defense Special Missile and Aeronautics Center (DEFSMAC/NSA) and NSA CSG rep to track Indications and Warnings (I&W) of impending Red and Grey space and missile launch activity. Fused SIGINT (COMINT), ELINT (telemetry), DSP (Infrared/thermal) data, IMINT, and OSINT to provide the Command Director and the Space and Missile Warning Center crews with intelligence needed to recommend a threat assessment to the National Command Authority. Monitored and reported on the launch preparations and movement of Russian Strategic Rocket Forces and ballistic missile and attack submarines. Tracked and reported on Russian long-range aviation activity and maintained situational awareness of ongoing conflicts in the Caucuses and elsewhere around the world. Tracked and reported all pending space re-entries that might be interpreted as an attack against North America and help the Intelligence Community track Russian and Chinese space surveillance capabilities. Monitored and reported Indications and Warnings related to the global Warning Problems and changes to the WATCHCON status.

description: Individually selected to spearhead the All-Source analysis effort for the Network Analysis Cell, CJ2 Kandahar Intelligence Fusion Center (KIFC), Combined Joint Task Force-10 (CJTF-10). Produced multiple Targeting Intelligence Packets/Target Support Packets, Social Network Diagrams, Interrogation Support Packets/ SDRs for detainee exploitation, and 400 RFIs incorporating GEOINT, SIGINT, Biometrics, TECHINT, and HUMINT in support of 10th Mountain and it’s subordinate units in Regional Command-South (RC-S) area of operations. Operated in coordination with OGA, NSA, NGA, DEA, DIA and FBI personnel to provide counterinsurgency support to Combined Joint Task Force-10 as the 10th MTN DIV (LI) Analysis and Control Element's (ACE) Master Analyst. Created, implemented, and supervised the Distributed Common Ground System – Army (DCGS-A) and ACE Block II system architecture for the RC-S Headquarters, applying first-ever employed designs to overcome regional-level challenges during combat operations. Personally directed the efforts of over 20 technical experts to field DCGS-A on the battlefield and commended by the ISAF CJ2 for excellence and technical expertise.

description: • Senior Intelligence Analyst and Senior Enlisted member of Joint Intelligence Center for Special Operations Command Central (SOCCENT). • Coordinated the development and provided quality control of intelligence products to support Army Special Forces Operational Detachments, Navy SEAL Teams, and Coalition Forces. • Managed production of Intelligence Summaries updating SOCCENT and Coalition SOF commanders with time-sensitive intelligence focusing on AOR wide terrorist organizations such as EAAQ, AIAI, JAM, IMU/IJU, and AQAM. • Fused information collected from tactical and national agencies into actionable intelligence products for SOF missions throughout the Area of Operations, developing target intelligence packets. • Managed the analytical efforts of seven service members to satisfy the Priority Intelligence Requirements and developed Intelligence Packets on specific High Value Targets and lethal aid related facilities. • Managed the J2 production schedule and products requirements. • Managed and maintained unit training programs forthe Korean Aerospace Operations Center (KAOC). • Directed intelligence wartime effort, matrixing intel experts across the KAOC as first ever enlisted Intelligence Duty Officer, position normally held by Capt or above. • Fused tailored ISR information into Strategy, Plans, and Operations divisions, responsible for prosecution of time sensitive targets prioritization and attack. • Principle advisor to commander for all intelligence support to Air Force Space Commanding General. • Performed in-depth space/missile threat research and analysis enhancing execution of SPACEAF weapon systems. • Conducted near-term and long-range analysis of global military intelligence for indications and warning. • Analyzed and maintained databases and products on adversary space reliance and terrestrial space targets. • Directed technical analysis of global adversary space launch and on-orbit space systems and capabilities.

description: Project Manager responsible for leading, mentoring, and training 28 analysts, including three subordinate managers. Combines all-source analysis with other intelligence disciplines for government client, supporting real-time counterterrorism operations and conducting target development. Compiled briefing materials for use in briefings to high-level government officials. Created time-sensitive all-source intelligence products related to the Global War on Terrorism (GWOT) and current counter-terrorism issues. Responsible for exploiting national assets in a 24x7, 365 day, work environment within a multi-agency program. Supported current counter-terrorism operations and frequently researched target areas related to the GWOT. Conducted interviews of new staff and potential managers, led new-employee on-boarding initiatives, generated training plans, completed employee evaluations, and ensured timely, accurate corporate billing on a U.S. Government contract valued over $400M.

description: Developed and produced intelligence products covering four provinces in northeastern Afghanistan. Recognized as the subject matter expert for Nangarhar Province in the 173rd Airborne Brigade during Operation Enduring Freedom. Worked with State Department, DEA, and British SAS teams that strengthened combined efforts in Nangarhar Province. Identified, developed, and created over 25 target packets resulting in the detention of numerous high value targets during Operation Enduring Freedom. Established the intelligence section of the Iraqi Army Mid-Euphrates Operations Center; resulting in the successful partnership between the 8th Iraqi Army Division intelligence officers and US forces during Operation Iraqi Freedom. Led a brigade level all source production section during Operation Iraqi Freedom, covering five provinces and consisting of joint service personnel specializing in HUMINT, SIGINT, MASINT, IMINT, and all-source analysts. Synchronized efforts with Special Operations, OGA, and DIA personnel.

description: A trustee of a partnership of two family trusts since April 1984. Served as the direct manager of this partnership, consisting of commercial and agricultural real estate assets valued at $12,000,000, from January 1993 to January 2002. Assets totaled 25 properties, consisting of 2 citrus groves and 10 commercial rental buildings serving up to forty tenants. Duties ranged from day-to-day property and office management activities to project development, budgeting and long range trust planning. Day-to-day activities required the supervision of seven employees and constructive interaction with tenants, prospective tenants, various trades, and local governmental officials. Development activities required the conceptualization, research, planning, permitting, costing, contracting, supervision and leasing of properties. Now supporting strategic planning and initiatives as a trustee.

description: The Center is an Army field operating agency. Directs and supervises four Division Chiefs and a 140 person military-civilian-contractor workforce responsible for the collection, preservation, recording, study, and publishing of the US Army's military history. Provides historical staff support to the Army Senior Leaders on all aspects of military history programs and policy, to include field museum operations. Responsible for the development and execution of a combined annual budget of $17 million. Oversees the production of the Army’s official histories and papers and studies for the Army staff and senior leaders on a range of topics affecting the Army.

description: Senior advisor to the commander, Afghan Border Police (ABP). Advised and coached the ABP commander and staff on operations, human resources, facilities, logistics and new equipment programs throughout the 11,687 man force engaged nationally in battling insurgency and organized crime. Synchronizes and coordinates police reform and operational activities with US forces, US interagency (State, OGA, Treasury, etc), ISAF, the UN, the European Union, individual donor nations and Afghan police, military, intelligence and civil authorities. Serves as the command Subject Matter Expert (SME) on border matters.

description: DoD and US European Command’s representative for security cooperation to the US Embassy in Ghana and the Ghana Armed Forces. Develops/implements/synchronizes security cooperation plans for the Embassy and USEUCOM by coordinating with DoS, DoD/services and other US agencies, host nation and foreign government officials to further US theater and regional goals. Managed the security cooperation component of the embassy’s country plan, coordinating with DoS, DoD/service departments, and host nation officials to shape/enhance US-Ghanaian relations. Manages a combined budget program of $9 million for Foreign Military Sales (FMS), Foreign Military Financing (FMF), International Military Education and Training (IMET), Humanitarian Assistance (HA), bilateral and regional training programs, such as the Africa Crisis Operations Training and Assistance (ACOTA) program and the Economic Community of West Africa States’ (ECOWAS) Kofi Annan International Peacekeeping Training Center, exercise related construction projects and the National Guard State Partnership Program (SPP). Implements all aspects of the Foreign Assistance and Arms Control Export Acts. Commended by the State Dept ACOTA PM for my execution of 3 training rotations and support to the program.

description: A self generated business born out of a 17 year hobby. As the owner and operator of an internet based business, I am solely responsible for all marketing and sales of antique and collectible militaria dating from WWI to the present day; receipts, book keeping, monetary transactions and accounting; inventory and stock of original military headgear, uniforms, field gear, and insignia as well as other artifacts. As the owner of the LHS, I understand the growing demand for military collectibles and endeavor to seek out desired artifacts making them available to novice and experienced collectors using legacy (military shows) and current marketing (internet) methods. The LHS gives back to the community by providing public historical displays at schools and at select historically oriented community events in North Carolina.

description: Civilian contract analyst forward deployed in support of CJTF-1 in Bagram Afghanistan; responsible for the production of Periodic Reviews, Source Reliability Assessments, CONOP input, answering RFI, and writing assessments; employed ARC Geographic Information System (GIS), Automated Message Handler Systems (M3 and Query Tree), CIDNE, Intelink, and Palantir to query reporting required in the development of daily intelligence products; retrieved data from Harmony, Source Operations Management Module (SOMM), Biometric Information Intelligence Reports Database (BIIR) during the development and evaluation of HUMINT source reliability assessments; provided BAF graphic threat updates concerning insurgent and terrorist activity depicting HUMINT threat stream reports concerning the base. Worked with a team of professionals to develop the Analytical and Intelligence support proposals for the Department of Defense; researches, analyzes, and inputs data into software programs to produce metrics for use in writing proposal narratives and descriptive tasks and orders; supports key players of the proposal team in the production of written and graphic products for use in written and oral presentations; periodically travels to SRA HQ to with company principles and executives during the deliberate proposal development.

description: Trends Analysis OIC, CIOC, C2, Multi-National Force – Iraq. Officer in charge of five military and DOD civilian analysts in support of OPERATION IRAQI FREEDOM. Supervises the research and maintenance of Combined Intelligence Operations Center (CIOC) Trends counterinsurgency metrics in multiple databases; develops trends analysis products and statistical data to support operational and executive-level analytical summaries, assessments, and briefings to the MNF-I Commanding General, DOD officials, and Iraqi leadership. Writes trends analysis intelligence papers and memorandums; trains analysts to use theater-wide automated SIGACTS and host nation reporting with digital mapping programs and commercial spreadsheet and database software programs. Provides analytical products to organizations throughout MNF-I, MNC-I, and numerous DOD agencies; provides data, assessments, and estimates to support the weekly MNF-I C2 round table and weekly MNF-I Commanding General briefing.

description: Officer in Charge and Senior Military Analyst for the Vietnam Analysis Section; manages and directs analysis and research efforts of assigned intelligence analysts investigating more than 2100 individual cases of personnel listed as Prisoner Of War or Missing In Action (POW/MIA); directs the review and evaluation of Field Investigation Reports, Reports of Unilateral Investigation, archive documents, and Current Investigation Reports for correlation to incidents of Americans still unaccounted-for as a result of the conflict in Southeast Asia. Produces investigative leads for joint and unilateral field investigations; plans and deploys to Vietnam as the senior team analyst during Joint Field Activities; coordinates with the US and Vietnamese government and military officials; maintains and correlates data from national agencies, Defense Prisoner of War/Missing Personnel Office (DPMO), Life Sciences Equipment Laboratory (LSEL), historical archives, and information derived from deployed investigation teams for use in developing investigation requirements; prepares written responses to quires from the U.S. Congress, Department of Defense, and the next of kin. Identifies collection requirements and provides analysis to deployed Investigation, Excavation, and Recovery Teams to provide the fullest accounting of missing Soldiers, Sailors, Airmen, and Marines resulting from the Vietnam War.

description: Chief of 20 analysts in the Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance-Analysis (ISR-A) Platoon for the Stryker Brigade Combat Team. Develops and validates intelligence concepts and doctrine for the Army’s first Interim Brigade Combat Team (IBCT). Integrates automated information systems in support of intelligence production efforts and maintains intelligence files and databases to provide intelligence support to the military decision-making process. Responsible for fusing combat information with intelligence gained from tactical, theater, and national products to produce tactically focused intelligence products to the IBCT/SBCT. Directs the ISR-A analytical effort to satisfy the Commanders PIR; is the primary trainer for platoon analysts concerning enemy order of battle, doctrine, predictive analysis, and operation of the All Source Analysts System - Remote Workstation (RWS); is the brigades Senior Master Analyst.

description: All Source Intelligence Technician. Supervises the All Source Production Section (ASPS) in the production of intelligence estimates, intelligence preparation of the battlefield products, target folders, and weekly intelligence updates; participates and contributes to planning meetings and mission development for division level exercises and real world contingency plans; establishes parameters and fuses information from the All Source Analysis System's (ASAS) multi-relational database for battle tracking enemy activity with multi-discipline reporting to produce intelligence reports for the Division Commanders warfighting effort; supervises and performs intelligence preparation of the battlefield; manages the employment of automated intelligence data processing systems; develops and executes intelligence training for 20 analysts; advises the commander and subordinate units on enemy situations, capabilities, vulnerabilities, and weather and terrain; responsible for the professional and technical development and welfare of the sections Paratroopers and NCOs. description:  Served as the NON-Commissioned Officer in charge of the Mosul Detention Facility (MDF) coordinating and supervising over 500 interrogations while managing 10 military and 2 civilian interrogators.  Coordinated with the Brigade S2X concerning all detainees for their intelligence values.  Reviewed, analyzed, and recommended final dispositions on 1000 detainees.  Provided oversight and approval of Interrogation Plans, reviewed Intelligence Information Reports (IIR), debriefed US/Coalition Forces, exploited documents and materials captured, conducted initial screening of detainees, coordinated interrogations for other government agencies (OGA), trained and approved new interrogators for interrogation operations, supervised numerous Category I and II interpreters used for interrogations, coordinated with the military police regarding all detainee operations, and conducted all interviews required by other intelligence disciplines for identification of High Value Targets (HVT).  Served as the Platoon Sergeant for 20 HUMINT Collectors.  Experienced with documentation research techniques, interviewing techniques, writing intelligence reports, assessing intelligence reports, building briefing materials, and coordinating information across all intelligence disciplines.  Experienced in providing advice on the collection, processing, reporting, analysis, evaluation, interpretation, and dissemination of intelligence information and or products.  Knowledgeable in the various intelligence collection assets and methods for U.S., friendly, non-hostile, and enemy entities.

description: I function as the team leader in charge of the oversight, mentoring, and recruitment of over 42 Afghan Local Nationals in both Herat and Farah Provinces. The ASCs consistently reported relevant atmospheric information which covered various topics to include narcotics, socio-economic pressures, insurgent and criminal networks, illicit trafficking, perceptions, and rumors in order to answer Host Nation Information Requirements for a wide range of cliental. I continually liaised with the Fusion Center of RC-West, US Military, Italian Military, Spanish Military, PRT, DoS, OGA’s, Special Operations TF’s, and other key elements in RC-W. Conducted daily missions in two or three member security teams to find, recruit, and train Afghan Sub-Contractors within both Herat and Farah Provinces including both rural and urban centers autonomous of military forces. I was also responsible for mobile force protection and personnel security of our team, VIP’s, and ASCs. I was responsible for maintaining a team operational budget, assigned weapons, and vehicles worth in excess of $65,000 monthly. Continually published over 210 Atmospheric Reports, Mosque Reports, and Market Reports monthly along with processing RFI’s on a daily basis. This position required familiarity and weapons qualification on both foreign and NATO primary and secondary weapon systems. This position required the ability to operate in austere environments in small teams away from military forces and the knowledge of the local culture and customs.

description: On a daily basis conducted face to face engagements with key actors and aggregates in a given geographic region to provide feedback and operational considerations to tactical and operational level commanders and their staff elements. I conducted Target Audience Analysis to sync with the targeting process in terms of Non-Kinetic applications to reach desired end states. I controlled numerous media centers during my 2nd Iraq tour in conjunction with PRT and DoS in order to provide refined messaging through indigenous forms of communication. I also coordinated with the U.S. Embassy, Joint Personal Recovery Center (JPRC), and Joint Interrogation Detention Center (JIDC) for implementation of PSYOP programs at the tactical level designed as short term influencing operations in support of DUSTWUN operations. I also served in a advising capacity for company and battalion commanders. Continually managed and mitigated 2nd and 3rd order effects across a wide spectrum of austere locations. Assisted in planning and executing over 400 combat missions during 2 tours in Iraq while operating in Anbar and Baghdad with various TF’s and USMC elements. Assisted in planning and executing over 175 combat missions in AFG in RC-EAST including Wardak, Logar, and Kunar Provinces while operating in conjunction with SOTFs and USMC. High levels of operational experience and Information Operations planning in C-IED, DOD Rewards Programs, and gathering atmospherics while operating in very high level threat areas including the AF-PAK border regions. Analyzed enemy propaganda (national media and locally printed) utilizing PSYOP SCAME/MARCO methods and advised commanders on the best Courses of Action to pursue in countering enemy propaganda. I served as an Assistant Team Leader for 1 year, Team Leader for 2 combat tours, and a 12 man jdetachment senior Non-Commissioned Officer my final year as a Psyop Soldier.

description: Responsible for training US ARMY and USMC soldiers (SOF/BCT and below) in the tactical level (F3EAD) process as it applies to Irregular Warfare. Primary responsibilities included teaching, mentoring, and advising as a subject matter expert in Non-Kinetic Targeting throughout the F3EAD process as a member of a 9 man targeting team with travel to both CONUS/OCONUS locations 75% of the time. This position included Warfighter Summits, ISR training, Guest Lectures, COIN Academies, Cultural Summits, Warfighter Symposiums, and instructing at the Strategic Intelligence Officers Course (SIOC). Utilized case studies, historical conflicts, current events, theory, and lessons learned to prepare soldiers for upcoming deployments to various conflict countries in support of GWOT operations combining SIGINT, ALL Source Intelligence, and Non-Kinetic targeting. Key focus was teaching Influence Operations, Information Operations, Atmospheric Analysis, Military Deception, Civil Military Operations, MAAWS, ISR Sync and Capabilities, and other aspects as they apply to Irregular Warfare. Supported DoS FID missions OCONUS in an advisory capacity. I accumulated over 600 hours instructing in a formal setting to soldiers with class sizes ranging from ten to over sixty.

description: NAVCO Sports Analysis and Coach George’s mission as a pitching instructor is to educate and train athletes, as well as their parents and coaches. Coach George is dedicated to creating a positive environment in which every athlete can reach their fullest potential. His goal is to educate athletes on mechanics, functional fitness, mental emotional training, and preparing them to compete while avoiding injury. NAVCO Sports Analysis is dedicated to finding the latest cutting edge research on pitching. Coach George consults on a regular basis with world renowned pitching coach, Dr. Tom House, The National Pitching Association (NPA) www.nationalpitching.net, and The Rod Dedeaux Research and Baseball Institute (RDRBI) http://www.rdrbi.com. .Tom has studied thousands of pitchers over the years, at all skill levels, using the latest in modern technology, and has identified 9 phases as key points of a pitching motion.

description: Laid off in restructure in December 2013. Site Contract Manager for a 75 person Line of Business for DRS Defense Solutions with $15M in annual sales and a $20M signature warrant. Develop, negotiate and manage multiple IDIQ and Research and Development contracts for SOCOM and Other Government Agencies (OGA) while ensuring compliance with corporate and government regulations. Provide complete Contracts support to include Subcontract Management and served as a DRS Small Business Liaison Officer (SBLO). • Provided two off site divisions of DRS with Contracts support for over fifty IDIQ / Government Contracts and Commercial Contracts/PO’s with sales totaling $30M annually. These contracts were primarily for product sales to prime contractors, the DoD, and Government Agencies. Product sales included 30% International sales and FMS contracts

description: From October 2012 to September 2013, I served as a Senior Counterintelligence Specialist and Team Lead of a five person Target Focused Analysis and Neutralization (TFAN) Team which conducted comprehensive intelligence operations and analysis in order to detect and mitigate "Insider Threats" (Green on Blue attacks) to Coalition Forces. I coordinated with and mentored Afghanistan National Army CI staff officers and National Directorate of Security officers for further target identification/exploitation. I performed biometrics and DNA collections; document/media/cell phone exploitations; administered Preliminary Creditability Assessment and Suitability (PCASS) examinations; conducted Counterintelligence screening/vetting operations; and made operational recommendations to Afghanistan National Security Forces and Security Forces Advisement and Assistance Teams. (Armed position) From September 2013 to June 2014, I served as a Senior Counterintelligence Support Specialist supporting Special Forces Advanced Operations Bases 1230 & 3120 (SOTF-SE), Gardez District, Paktiya Province, AFG. I routinely conducted intelligence missions such as screening Locally Employed Personnel, administering PCASS examinations, and screening/vetting operations of Afghanistan National Army Special Operations Forces. I advised SOTF-SE command of findings and make recommendations of employment termination, Coalition Forces base denial, and disqualifications from training of Afghan National Security Forces and nominated individuals be placed on the Biometrics Enabled Watch List based on insurgent affiliation/associations. I also conducted debriefings, intelligence liaison with military units/U.S. national level agencies, provided support to Operational Security/Threat Awareness and Reporting programs, security/ vulnerability assessments, initial handling of walk-in sources, spot/assess individuals for source operations, and performed intelligence report writing/ quality control.

description: Served as a Senior Intelligence Analyst supporting International Security Assistance Force-Joint Command, Information Dominance Center, Governance Section, I conducted research and analysis in order to provide a comprehensive Common Operating Picture of the Afghanistan Governance system at National, Regional, Provincial, and District levels; I gathered, integrated, and evaluated trends in Government and Politics; identified Positive, Negative, Neutral and Potential influencers; tracked leadership changes at Ministry, Region, Province, and District levels; reviewed open-source media and classified message traffic for input in the daily information summary; and conducted assessments regarding the Government of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan’s ability to provide security, improved governance and socio-economic development in order to protect the Afghan people and provide a secure environment for sustainable peace and transition from ISAF assisted to Afghan lead.

description: Served as a Human Intelligence (HUMINT) analyst responsible for providing analytical support and conducting comprehensive research on complex insurgent and terrorist networks associated with Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs). Developed analytical strategies and produce targeting related assessments and target support packages in collaboration with DoD, interagency, and Coalition partners to include COIC, CITP and other related organizations conducting all-source fused intelligence analysis of insurgent networks and associated technical signatures supporting counterinsurgency/ corruption operations. Responsible for developing processes of collecting information and identifying emerging threats, analyzing historical trends, and fusing multiple forms and sources of intelligence to provide commanders and decision makers with the intelligence needed to enhance Afghanistan's stability.

description: Routinely operated “outside the wire”, autonomous of Coalition Forces, as a Military Analyst who employed and managed a network of local national advisors across a wide spectrum of Afghan society for the purpose of collecting “atmospheric” information regarding local perceptions on a wide variety of subjects concerning personal/local security; Afghan Security Forces; price and availability of goods; informal public perception sampling as well as “street talk”; availability and performance of essential services/government services; infrastructure rehabilitation; the current political situation; potentially newsworthy information; significant religious events; tribal issues; and situations affecting stability, support and reconstruction efforts. Provided information, technical assistance, analysis, recommendations and professionally written products to commanders and unit staffs for non-kinetic operational planning and developing programs that foster mutual trust and understanding between multi-national forces and the Afghan people; gauged effectiveness of civil military operations, information operation products, and media campaigns; and facilitated access to officials in the government and “influence targets” within selected communities.

description: Directly participated in Time Sensitive Targeting and Ground Assault Force missions providing tactical/ sensitive site exploitation, crime scene investigations, evidence collection/ exploitation, and pre/ post blast site exploitation of improvised explosive device (IED) events to uncover and target the operational, financial and social networks of insurgent groups. Conducted asymmetric, multi-intelligence threat analysis and fusion of insurgent/criminal networks intelligence for targeting purposes in support of the Joint Improvised Explosive Device Defeat Organization’s (JIEDDO) “attack the network” mission.

description: Supported military units in conducting non-lethal operations by conversing with the local population and performing analysis of gathered information, thus allowing the unit to better understand the population’s political, economic and social needs, and to understand the history of particular tribes and social groups in their area of operations. Efforts helped develop more effective courses of actions, such as providing security, essential services, and economic development opportunities to the civilian population in order to encourage the civilian population to support the host nation government and reduce their support for insurgent groups.

description: Routinely operated “outside the wire”, autonomous of Coalition Forces, as a Military Analyst who employed and managed a network of local national advisors (sources) across a wide spectrum of Iraqi society for the purpose of collecting “atmospheric” information regarding local Iraqi perceptions on a wide variety of subjects concerning personal/local security; Iraqi Security Forces, Iraqi Army, and Iraqi Police performance; price and availability of goods; informal public perception sampling as well as “street talk”; availability and performance of essential services/ government services; infrastructure rehabilitation; the current political situation; potentially newsworthy information gathering; significant religious events; tribal issues; and situations affecting stability, support and reconstruction efforts. Provided information, technical assistance, analysis, recommendations and professionally written products to commanders and unit staffs for planning operations and developing programs that foster mutual trust and understanding between multi-national forces and the Iraqi people; gauged effectiveness of civil Military operations, IO/ PSYOPs products, and media campaigns; and facilitates access to officials in the government and “influence targets” within selected communities.
